{
  format: 1
  name: downgrade-shape-compatible-no-transform-unspecified
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#evolution", "#annex-e"]
  tags: [version, replay]
  note: '''
    Companion to `downgrade-drops-populated-field-rejected`, probing the other
    side of the §20.2 clause. The active 1.1.0 adds an OPTIONAL private field
    `region` (text?) that no row populates, then a downgrade to 1.0.0 removes
    it. §20.2's rejection clause fires only "when the older shape cannot
    represent the current live values and no declared downgrade transform
    preserves them" — here there are no live `region` values, so the older
    shape can represent the current live state and the rejection clause does not
    apply. But §20.2's first sentence says a downgrade "applies an explicit
    direct migration or available exact inverses," and does not state whether
    the §20.1 compatible same-identity auto-copy alone suffices for a downgrade
    with no data loss and no declared transform. Whether this downgrade commits
    or is rejected for lacking an explicit transform is not pinned by SPEC.md.
  '''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.compat.downok@1.1.0"
    $model: {
      companies: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        name: "text"
        region: "text?"
      }
      $public: {
        companies: { $view: ".companies { id, name }" }
      }
    }
    // no row populates `region` (it is none for every row)
    $data: { companies: { acme: { name: "Acme" } } }
  }

  steps: [
    { host_load: {
        package: {
          $liasse: 1
          $app: "t.compat.downok@1.0.0"
          $model: {
            companies: {
              $key: "id"
              id: "text"
              name: "text"
            }
            $public: {
              companies: { $view: ".companies { id, name }" }
            }
          }
          $data: { companies: { acme: { name: "Acme" } } }
        }
      }
      expect: {
        outcome: unspecified
        detail: "downgrade removes an unpopulated optional field with no declared transform; §20.2 does not pin whether the compatible auto-copy alone permits the downgrade"
      } }
  ]
}
